---
// FAQ teaser section for the homepage. Surfaces 3–4 highest-objection
// items from the canonical /faq/ page as native HTML <details>
// collapsibles (no JS). Each item links to the matching #fragment on
// /faq/ for the full answer; the canonical answer lives at /faq/.
//
// Order is deliberate: vs spec-kit → why CLI → naming → token savings.
// The first two are positioning; the second two address brand and
// evidence.
---

<section class="faq-teaser section" aria-labelledby="faq-teaser-title">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 id="faq-teaser-title" class="faq-teaser__title">
      Got questions?
    </h2>
    <p class="faq-teaser__lead">
      Here are the questions people keep asking. Each links to the full
      answer on the <a href="/faq/" class="faq-teaser__indexlink">FAQ page</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="faq-teaser__list">
      <details class="faq-teaser__item">
        <summary class="faq-teaser__q">
          How is SpecScore different from spec-kit?
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-teaser__a">
          <p>
            spec-kit is a methodology; SpecScore is a storage format
            for the specs you write, plus a CLI. They compose — a
            spec-kit extension that writes SpecScore is in flight.
          </p>
          <a href="/faq/#vs-spec-kit" class="faq-teaser__more">
            Full answer →
          </a>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-teaser__item">
        <summary class="faq-teaser__q">
          How are SpecStudio Skills different from Superpowers and agent-skills?
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-teaser__a">
          <p>
            Similar in spirit — all three guide AI agents through ideate
            → specify → plan → implement. SpecStudio Skills writes
            artifacts in the SpecScore format and uses the
            <code>specscore</code> CLI for queries and status changes;
            the others read and write files directly. Pick SpecStudio
            when token consumption matters.
          </p>
          <a href="/faq/#vs-superpowers" class="faq-teaser__more">
            Full answer →
          </a>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-teaser__item">
        <summary class="faq-teaser__q">
          Why a CLI — can I not just install skills?
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-teaser__a">
          <p>
            Skills cannot reliably enforce referential integrity,
            return filtered queries without reading every file, or
            mutate the right status field at the right time. The CLI
            does each in one call. Skills read every file to do the
            same.
          </p>
          <a href="/faq/#why-cli" class="faq-teaser__more">
            Full answer →
          </a>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-teaser__item">
        <summary class="faq-teaser__q">
          Why "SpecScore" — what does it score?
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-teaser__a">
          <p>
            Two readings, both intended. Partitura — a structured
            score of requirements. And a literal quality grade — the
            CLI linter is the deterministic score, and the
            <code>/score</code> skill is the AI-judged A–F readiness
            grade.
          </p>
          <a href="/faq/#naming" class="faq-teaser__more">
            Full answer →
          </a>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-teaser__item">
        <summary class="faq-teaser__q">
          Where are the token-savings numbers?
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-teaser__a">
          <p>
            A measured side-by-side comparison is in flight before the
            Habr post. Structurally: the CLI returns a small structured
            list; a vanilla agent reads N documents instead.
          </p>
          <a href="/faq/#token-savings" class="faq-teaser__more">
            Full answer →
          </a>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-teaser { background: var(--cream); }
  .faq-teaser__title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .faq-teaser__lead {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 50ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .faq-teaser__indexlink {
    color: var(--ink-blue);
    border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
  }

  .faq-teaser__list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  .faq-teaser__item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .faq-teaser__item[open] {
    background: var(--cream-2);
  }
  .faq-teaser__q {
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    padding: var(--space-3);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .faq-teaser__q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-teaser__q::after {
    content: "+";
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1;
    transition: transform 160ms ease;
  }
  .faq-teaser__item[open] .faq-teaser__q::after {
    content: "−";
  }
  .faq-teaser__q:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--ink-blue);
    outline-offset: -2px;
  }

  .faq-teaser__a {
    padding: 0 var(--space-3) var(--space-3);
  }
  .faq-teaser__a p {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .faq-teaser__a code {
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 0.05em 0.3em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .faq-teaser__more {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--ink-blue);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
  }
</style>
